# PART I: THE ARTIT INVARIANT — FINAL FORM

## I.1 The Limit Theorem

For the six fundamental constants π, e, φ, √2, γ, Ω:

```
lim_{N→∞} P(N) = 1000/32 = 31.25
```

where:

```
P(N) = ∏_{K∈{π,e,φ,√2,γ,Ω}} [ 1000 × (K_frac)⁻³ / reverse_N(K_frac) + 2K - 6 - S_K/6 ]
```

and reverse_N takes the first N digits of K_frac and reverses them, adding the integer part of K divided by 10.

