# PART II: THE ALGORITHMIC FRAMEWORK

## II.1 The Core Algorithm — ArtitInvariantEngine

```
function ArtitInvariantEngine(constants_list, N):
    product = 1
    for each K in constants_list:
        K_frac = fractional_part(K)
        digits = first_N_digits(K_frac)
        reversed_digits = reverse(digits)
        R = integer(reversed_digits) + floor(K)/10
        T = 1000 × (K_frac)^(-3) / R
        C = 2K - 6 - (sister_of(K))/6
        L = T + C
        product = product × L
    return product
```

## II.2 The Sister Pairing Function

```
function sister_of(K):
    match K:
        case π: return e
        case e: return π
        case φ: return √2
        case √2: return φ
        case γ: return Ω
        case Ω: return γ
        case else: return null
```

## II.3 The Reverse Digit Function

```
function reverse_N(K_frac, N):
    str = string(K_frac)[2:N+2]  # skip "0."
    reversed_str = reverse(str)
    return integer(reversed_str)
```

